comments.body:
@lsm5 I see testing-farm tests failing on F43/rawhide now, e.g. https://artifacts.dev.testing-farm.io/8be93fae-957e-41cf-963e-344e0daa8673/ in “signing” because of an unexpected “Missing key” error text.

I think that’s because the CI images use `rust-podman-sequoia` 0.1.0, and the RPMs are now 0.2.0 (specifically https://github.com/ueno/podman-sequoia/pull/7/commits/d41fefaa1fa35ee56c6a3aac0105232733460932 replaces the expected “was not found” error message).

It would be cleanest to update the CI images to 0.2.0, _and_ to include `rust-podman-sequoia` in the F43 image, for consistency — but, short-term, that should be coordinated with https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/27017#issuecomment-3267081316 .
